{"article_id":"9K67eFmT0dwbGxNq","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"As the fallout from the first diagnosed case of Ebola in New York continues to reverberate throughout the densely populated region ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"political leaders are grappling with the deeply conflicting impulses","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"the virus evokes .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"On one hand , the Obama administration and other public officials ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"following the lead of health experts ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"have tried to calm public anxiety","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"- directly addressing the impulse","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"to flee from those","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"who have been diagnosed","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"or to prevent the arrival of others","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"who might be .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"But recent decisions by the governors of New York and New Jersey show the other side of the equation .","depth":5},{"id":12,"text":"As elected officials","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"governing a jittery public ,","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"they have gone beyond what","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"health officials say","depth":11},{"id":16,"text":"is necessary","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"in imposing a three-week mandatory quarantine for everyone","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"who has come into direct contact with Ebola patients while in West Africa .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"To health officials , they have potentially hurt America 's Ebola response","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"by stigmatizing health workers for no accepted medical reason .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Workers","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"who could help quell the outbreak in Africa","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"might decide not to put up with such conditions ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the thinking goes .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"But public pressure is high .","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Although there have been only four confirmed diagnoses of Ebola on US soil ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"4 in 10 Americans worry","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"that they or a family member might contract the virus ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"and wide majorities still support travel restrictions on those","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"returning from west Africa ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"polls find .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Moreover , public confidence in the federal government 's ability","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"to handle Ebola","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"is dropping ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"according to a recent Gallup poll .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"An unscientific poll on NJ.com on Monday afternoon showed","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"that 55 percent of respondents said","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"New Jersey Gov . Chris Christie is doing the best job","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"of responding to the Ebola crisis .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"President Obama was second at 20 percent .","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"\" It is common for the public to favor a policy action","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"that on its face seems like it will be effective ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"but which experts warn us against","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and suggest","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"may prove to be counterproductive , \"","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"writes Jeanne Zaino , professor of political campaign management at New York University , in an opinion article in Newsday .","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"\" In these instances , the polls are driven by fear","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"and it is incumbent on elected officials to weigh the evidence","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"and make the best decision possible","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"- not the most politically expedient decision ,","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"but the one","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that is in the best interest of our health and safety . \"","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"Both Governor Christie and New York Gov . Andrew Cuomo have backtracked a bit","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"after facing intense pressure from health experts and the Obama administration .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"On Monday morning , New Jersey health department officials announced","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"that Kaci Hickox , the nurse","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"who had been held against her will in a tent outside a New Jersey medical center over the weekend","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"and the first","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"to fall under the new policy ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"would be discharged","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and allowed to fly home in a private flight to Maine .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"And on Sunday , Governor Cuomo announced","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"he would ease some of the details of the state ' s restrictive new quarantine policy","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"- the second time in three days","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"he has seemed to backtrack on his public health decisions .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Those","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"who had contact with Ebola patients","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"while in West Africa ,","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"but were not showing any symptoms ,","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"would be allowed to be quarantined at home rather than a hospital ,","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"the governor said .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"Those quarantined would also be compensated for lost income ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"This came","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"after the governor joined New York City Mayor Bill de Blasio on Thursday at the announcement","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"that a Manhattan doctor","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"who had just returned from volunteering in Guinea","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"had been diagnosed .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"He said","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"the state was well prepared ,","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"it had learned from the mistakes of Dallas ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"and citizens had nothing to fear .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Still , the very next day , Cuomo blindsided New York City officials and the Obama administration ,","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"joining Christie , a Republican and likely presidential aspirant ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"to impose the mandatory quarantine for anyone","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"deemed \" high risk \"","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"of carrying the virus","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"- a quarantine","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"that had not been part of any of the plans","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"mapped out","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"and drilled for weeks in New York City .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"The announcement outraged New York City officials behind the scenes ,","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"The New York Times reported ,","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"and the Obama administration said on Monday","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"it had \" concerns \" about the policy .","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"On Friday , Mr. Obama hugged Nina Pham , the Dallas nurse","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"who had just been declared Ebola-free .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"She had treated Thomas Duncan , the first American","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"diagnosed with Ebola on US soil ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"and the only person","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"to die of the disease in the US .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"The president ' s photo op last Friday underscored the administration ' s hope","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"to alleviate the fear of contagion","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"and to celebrate health workers ' efforts .","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"Ms. Hickox ,","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"who had been volunteering with the humanitarian group Doctors Without Borders ,","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"had been protesting her confinement ,","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"calling it \" inhumane \" and a violation of her basic human rights .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"She had also hired a legal team","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"to fight for her release this weekend ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"since she showed no symptoms","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"and had twice tested negative for the virus ,","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"there were no legal grounds","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"to keep her confined in an isolated tent with only a portable toilet and no shower facilities or a TV .","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"New York Mayor de Blasio ,","depth":5},{"id":118,"text":"while straining to avoid the appearance of deep divisions among regional officials ,","depth":5},{"id":119,"text":"nevertheless distanced himself from the quarantine policy .","depth":4},{"id":120,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":7},{"id":121,"text":"you care about","depth":7},{"id":122,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":6},{"id":125,"text":"`` Anyone","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"who has heard nurse Hickox explain her situation in her proud , compassionate , intelligent voice","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"knows","depth":8},{"id":128,"text":"that what happened to her was inappropriate , ''","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"de Blasio said over the weekend .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"`` Each government has to make decisions .","depth":7},{"id":131,"text":"We understand that ....","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"But the problem here is this hero is coming back from the front ,","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"having done the right thing ,","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"was treated with disrespect","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"was treated with a sense","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"that she had done something wrong","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"when she had n't .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"We owe her better than that . \"","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"Both Christie and Cuomo , too , have urged Americans to see those","depth":6},{"id":140,"text":"volunteering on the front lines","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"as heroes , not pariahs ,","depth":5},{"id":142,"text":"and have emphasized","depth":5},{"id":143,"text":"that all evidence shows","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"that the only way","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"to contract Ebola","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"involves direct , intimate contact with victims","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"who are showing symptoms .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":295,"left":200,"right":294,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":150,"right":199,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":0,"right":149,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":178,"right":198,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":178,"left":157,"right":177,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":157,"left":152,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":3,"right":151,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":151,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":6,"right":155,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":153,"right":154,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":11,"right":176,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":169,"right":175,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":163,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":161,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":158,"right":160,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":12,"right":13,"relat